        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The Indian currency displays as Rp, which is wrong, and not as Rs. which is the correct symbol.\nThis issue was raised in Issue ZF-6795, where Thomas Weidner pointed out that the source was the Unicode CLDR database, where the symbol for the Indian Rupee was \"Rp.\". \nHowever, as the person who raised this issue originally pointed out, Unicode corrected the problem(Bug 2239)  in their latest release, 1.7.1: http:\/\/www.unicode.org\/cldr\/bugs\/locale-bugs\/closed?expression=target.*1\\.7\\.1\nHowever, Zend Framework 1.9.0 has been released with CLDR 1.7 which has the bug, and not with CLDR 1.7.1 where the bug has been fixed.\n\nThe result is that applications developed for the Indian market using the Zend Framework all have this bug, which is very irritating."
        },
